              "text": "This chapter provides a foundational understanding of sustainable energy finance, exploring its critical role in the global energy transition. It examines the current dynamics of energy markets and the economic and policy factors shaping renewable energy investments. Key topics include global trends in energy finance, the increasing role of ESG (Environmental, Social, and Governance) considerations, and the challenges of aligning financial flows with sustainable development goals. It also discusses how market dynamics, such as fluctuating energy prices and technological advancements, impact investment decisions."
